In data2004, the mean daily PM2.5 concentration in california is 10.10 and median is 13.13, but the max value is 251.00, which seems odd at first. However, after researching, any values below 500.4 ug/m3 is considered as valid quantity to have for PM2.5. The minimum value is -0.10, and after researching, the minimum values for PM2.5 should be 0. In data2019, the mean is 7.744, median is 6.500, but the max is 120.900. The minimum value is -2.200, which should not be the case. There are no missing values for data2004 and data2019.

I ordered the dataset to look at the data. Any negative values should not be there. I removed any points with negative PM2.5 values from both datasets. Then, I confirmed that both datasets do not contain any negative values of daily mean PM2.5 concentration.
